President Biden met with FEMA Administrator Deanne Criswell, Dr. Anthony Fauci, Liz Sherwood-Randall, and Jeff Zients, along with members of the Homeland Security and COVID-19 Response teams, to discuss the COVID-19 pandemic in hurricane-prone states in the South and Southeast. They talked about protecting public health, enhancing preparedness, and adapting response and recovery operations to address the challenges of hurricanes and the Delta variant. The President was briefed on the importance of vaccination as a preparatory step for peak hurricane season and discussed FEMA's efforts to provide COVID-safe sheltering, vaccination options, and workforce protection.